[[Turkmen language|Turkmen]] ([[Turkic language]] / [[Oghuz language]] ) is the [[official language]] of Turkmenistan (per the [[Constitution of Turkmenistan|1992 Constitution]]), although [[Russian language|Russian]] still is widely spoken in cities as a "language of inter-ethnic communication".
Turkmen is spoken by 72% of the population, Russian 12%, [[Uzbek language|Uzbek]] 9%,<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2098.html CIA Website]</ref> and other languages 7%.
